 <table-wrap-foot class="table-wrap-foot">
  <p class="p">Comments:</p>
  <p class="p">• Average aquifer mean parameters (depth, porosity) are taken from hydrogeological reports and field data.</p>
  <p class="p">• 
   <italic class="italic">R</italic>/
   <italic class="italic">P</italic>—ratio among available water resources (
   <italic class="italic">R</italic>) and rainfall (
   <italic class="italic">P</italic>) taken as total recharge ratio in the mass balance model for alluvial aquifers
  </p>
  <p class="p">• The aquifer inflow/outflow rate is estimated as the product of rainfall magnitude times the 
   <italic class="italic">R</italic>/
   <italic class="italic">P</italic> value.
  </p>
  <p class="p">• Average crop nitrogen uptake is estimated using the values given in Appendix 
   <xref rid="Tab6" ref-type="table" class="xref">3</xref>.
  </p>
  <p class="p">• Total nitrate mass input considers the maximum allowed nitrogen mass per year by the EU Nitrates Directive (170 kg N/ha/year), the crop area, and the average nitrogen uptake.</p>
